# Keep the Docker build context lean. The Dockerfile `COPY . .` ships the whole workspace (it needs
# gui/scripts/lib + packages/*/src to build), so prune everything the build re-creates or never uses.
#
# NOTE: paths are relative to the BUILD CONTEXT root. Run the build with the repo root as context and
# this file as -f deploy/control-vm/Dockerfile … (or copy this .dockerignore to the repo root as
# .dockerignore for the build — see README.md).

# VCS + editor
.git
.gitignore
**/.DS_Store

# All node_modules (pnpm reinstalls in the build stage from the lockfile)
node_modules
**/node_modules

# Build outputs (the build stage regenerates dist + gui/dist)
**/dist
**/build
gui/dist
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Claude Code dev tooling — the WHOLE dir (worktrees, settings.local.json, any MCP/token config). The
# image never needs it, and settings could hold credentials — so it must NEVER enter the build context.
.claude
**/.claude
deploy/e2b/node_modules
deploy/daytona/node_modules

# Test/coverage/log noise
**/coverage
**/.vitest
**/*.log
npm-debug.log*

# Local env / secrets / credentials — NEVER ship these into an image. The Dockerfile hands EVERY secret
# (PIFLOW_TOKEN, the pi gateway key, CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN) in at RUNTIME via `fly secrets set`; none is
# ever baked. This block is the belt-and-suspenders guard so a stray secret file can't ride `COPY . .` in.
.env
.env.*
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/.credentials.json
# npm/registry auth (an _authToken in an .npmrc would otherwise persist in the image)
**/.npmrc
# private keys / certs / cloud + shell credential stores
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/*.p12
**/*.pfx
**/id_rsa*
**/id_ed25519*
**/.ssh
**/.aws
**/.netrc
**/*.env
**/secrets.json
**/*.secret

# Runs + collected data (never bake a product's data; see CLAUDE.md data boundaries)
**/.pi
**/.piflow/*/runs
